Responsibilities:

Reporting to senior leadership, this role will assume responsibilities for spearheading marketing and communications strategy and execution for the Park.  Other major functions of this job include:
Develop integrated marketing and communications strategy that supports and advances the brand awareness and advocacy of the Park and drives positive mindshare that can contribute to the development of the ecosystem in the Park; 
Drive external relationships and proactive engagement with local and international stakeholders including relevant government departments, regulatory bodies, universities, R&D institutions, industry leaders and NGOs to lobby for their support for the Park’s vision and strategic imperatives; 
Support business development activities through organizing industry, marketing and community events which engage and appeal to local and overseas tech ventures and startups, incubators, accelerators and top entrepreneurs and talents as well as facilitating partnerships, business matching and corporate engagements;
Responsible for public affairs, issue and crisis management; taking a proactive role in identifying potential issues, evaluating reputation risks and providing recommendations and communications plans for the senior management; 
Develop compelling messaging for corporate announcements and speaking platforms; and work closely with the Park’s Chairperson, CEO and other senior leaders to develop content assets, not limited to keynote presentations, social media posts, thought leadership pieces spanning across paid, owned and earned media platforms;
Perform other duties and tasks assigned by Supervisor and CEO.

Requirements:

Degree in Marketing, Communications, Business or related subjects, with at least 12 years of experience in PR, communications, business development and marketing positions, preferably gained in MNC / sizable companies.
Strong track record in strategic brand management, reputation management and stakeholder engagements for respected companies preferably with presence in Greater China, Greater Bay Area and/or globally.
Good understanding and appreciation of technology trends.  Ability to work with global and local technology ventures and startups and provide value-added advice and support to them for promoting their innovations.
Profound understanding and hands-on experience on government relations and excellent in strategic thinking and able to drive the Park’s corporate narratives that align with various business priorities.
Possess the ability to work with diverse categories of stakeholders and excellent communications skills that can command impact when interacting with industry players, academia, board members and other key stakeholders etc.
Strong business acumen, problem solving and leadership skills with excellent command of spoken/written English and Chinese (including Putonghua).

Responsibilities:

Assist in marketing reports preparation and data analysis, gather insights in customer behavior and business trend to improve the performance and drives sales;
Assist the Marketing Manager in the preparation of expense report, cost and budget report;
Work closely with marketing and sales departments in launching new product programs and execution and completion of projects;
Develop the marketing plan for products that support in conjunction with Sales & Marketing team, including key activities and budgets to support the acquisition of new customers and retention of existing customers;
Collaborate with various internal and external parties to ensure smooth execution of event promotion and operation.
Requirements:

Degree holder in Marketing, Business Administration, or other related discipline;
Minimum 3 years of working experience in marketing or sales related discipline;
Work experience in HORECA, Frozen Meat and food Trading business is an advantage;
Experience in Adobe Illustrator, Photoshop, Facebook, Instagram, Twitter, Wechat, and search engine marketing is a plus but not a must;
Proficient in PC applications, including MS Word, PowerPoint and Excel;

Creative and well-organized with excellent analytical and problem-solving skills;
Excellent communication and presentation skills;
Able to excel in fast-paced and dynamic environment with tight deadlines;
Self-motivated, result-oriented team player;
Proficient in Chinese and English.

We offer competitive remuneration and fringe benefits including discretionary bonus, medical insurance, annual leave and 5-day work. Interested party please send detailed resume in both Chinese and English version with expected salary & date of availability by clicking "Apply Now".

Personal data will be used for recruitment purpose only.

Job Description

Locate new business opportunities as potential digital marketing products both independently and under the guidance of team leader;
Prospecting, identifying and acquiring new HK based clients for selling online marketing advertising solutions (e.g. WeChat/China Advertising/China KOLs,etc);
Follow up sales Leads, prepare sales pitch and agreements with marketing team;
Maintain good relationships with clients, regular review and up-selling various advertising solutions to enhance their advertising performance/effect;
Execute inhouse media investment plan by working closely with Marketing Director to enhance the market impact of Our Company;
Manage clients’ projects, including defining deliverables, schedule and setting milestones, resources planning, coordinating internal resources, expectation management, launch, KPI tracking and post-campaign evaluation, etc.

The Successful Applicant

1-4 years Sales or Marketing / Advertising / PR experience;
Online-media savvy is a big advantage;
Knowledge in China media (social media, KOLs, Tencent, Douyin, Xiaohongshu, Video platform, etc), but not a must, training will be delivered;
Creative, Dynamic, embracing changes personally;
Good communication skills in both English & Chinese;
Immediate availability is preferred;
Candidate with higher qualification and relevant working experience will be considered as Senior Business Development Executive / Assistant Business Development Manager.

What's On Offer

Attractive Remuneration Package and Benefits
Incentive & commission schemes will be offered
5-day work
Bank Holidays and other special leave (e.g. Birthday Leave, Wedding Leave and Family Leave, etc.)
Medical Insurance
Sales and Product training will be provided
Team Building Activities
Opportunity for Job Promotion
Friendly Work Environment
Interest parties please send your CV with availability, current and expected salary to us.

**Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only**

Responsibilities:

Develop PR and branding, marketing strategies for the Center from scratch;
Design, execute and perform tracking of PR, branding and marketing programs;
Promote the Center through different channels including website, e-newsletter, social media, printed and electronic media, etc;
Handle PR and media relations such as interviews and media activities; maintain good relations with the media;
Collaborate and communicate with the University partners, local and overseas research collaborators, and the industry to promote our company.
Organize various kinds of events and workshops e.g. conferences, award ceremonies, seminars, public events, planning, budget control, execution and event logistics

Requirements:

A bachelor or higher degree preferably in business, communication, marketing, public relations, or science;
 At least 5 years’ experience in PR or marketing fields and experience in social media and writing would be an advantage;
Smart, mature, organized with pleasant personality and strong interpersonal skills;
Attentive to details, creative, independent, proactive and flexible to meet tight schedule;
Possess excellent communication skills, media relations experience and network;
Proficiency in the design and production of marketing materials; Basic knowledge of graphic design and proficient in Adobe Photoshop, Illustrator and PowerPoint;
Good command of spoken & written English and Chinese.

We offer a competitive package & career prospect to the right candidate. Qualified and interested parties, please send application quoting the above reference number and detailing contact information, education and employment background, and salary expectation via : “APPLY NOW”

Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. For more information, please be welcome to visit our ：website: www.hkstarlite.com /  https://teamgreenworld.net/

Personal data provided will be used for consideration of your application for the applied position and other suitable vacancies in the Starlite Group.

Responsibilities:

Responsible for following up tenders / quotations / proposals;
Liaise with various project teams to facilitate the preparation of tender and quotation submissions;
Maintain good relationships with existing clients and follow up with prospects;
Assist in organising seminars and business development activities as needed;
Perform administrative and marketing duties as assigned.


Requirements:

Bachelor’s degree in Marketing, Engineering, Environmental Services or related disciplines;
Minimum of 2 years of relating work experience, preferably in an engineering, environmental services or construction industry;
Business development experience preferred;
Proactive and customer-oriented and a good team player;
Must have demonstrated strong interpersonal skills and ability to build relationships at all levels.

Responsibilities

Create, execute and coordinate marketing program materials, communications, graphics, brand website maintenance, digital/social media strategy and events/exhibitions;
Execute social media marketing ad strategies on Instagram, Facebook, LinkedIn, Pinterest Twitter and YouTube;
Manage and maintain website content using HTML or other web content management interface;
Prepare media plan, budget summary and execute advertisement campaign with reports;
Report on the performance of different paid media platform and provide campaign insights to assess campaign effectiveness and identify optimization opportunities;
Coordinate with Design, PR and Communications and other functional teams to ensure brand consistency and smoothness operations;
Other ad hoc tasks as assigned.

 Requirements

Degree holder in marketing or related disciplines; 
3 years or above experiences in digital marketing;
Knowledge in Google Adwords / Facebook AD manager is an advantage;
Knowledge of Photoshop or AI is an advantage;
Good communication in spoken and written English and Chinese and Mandarin;
Immediate available is preferred.

Role Summary:

With the aim to diversify our business, our management is actively developing opportunities in other business sectors. 

To copy with our growth, we are looking for a high caliber candidate for the position of Assistant Manager, Marketing and Research Analytics.

Responsibilities:

Responsible for all-round market research across different potential industries including data collection, figures analysis and market trend forecast;
Conduct in-depth analysis covering business models, customers’ preferences and needs, branding and risk assessment;
Provide regular market intelligence and competitors analysis for strategic planning and decision making;
Prepare periodical reports in sales performance analysis, budgeting, costing and forecasting;
Perform ad-hoc tasks as required.

 Requirements:

Degree holder in Business Administration, Marketing, Finance or related discipline;
Minimum 5 years of experience in market research and data analysis;
Knowledge and experience in merger & acquisition, franchise, emerging business is highly preferred;
Strong business sense, analytical, detail-oriented and self-initiative;
Enthusiastic, sensitive in market changes and future trends, able to use initiative to come up with new ideas;
Good command of spoken and written English, Cantonese and Putonghua;
Able to travel when required.

Our client is a well-established food distributor representing a number of prestigious Japanese FMCG/food brands and having good market share in Hong Kong. 
In line with their business development, they now require a responsible and detail-minded talent to join their team as Merchandising Officer.  The caliber with less years of relavant working experiences will be considered as Assistant Merchandising Officer.

 Responsibilities:

Handle merchandising & sourcing matters, such as purchasing, suppliers, inventory;
Responsible for logistics/warehouse operation and stock-take operation regularly;
Coordinate in purchasing operation with Japan or overseas offices;
Handle shipping cost calculation, quality control on products importing to Hong Kong;
Assist in marketing events & regular stock operations

Requirements:

Tertiary education in buying/purchasing or business relating discipline;
At least 5 years working experience in purchasing/product control, especially in Food & Beverage / Retailing industry;
Good command in spoken English and Cantonese;
Excellent language literacy (both spoken and written) in Japanese is highly preferable;
Proficient in MS Office, Sage Accpac knowledge an advantage;
Detailed-minded and good problem solving skills with strong sense of responsibility
